# No instructional UI copy

When editing `apps/web` user-facing pages and Khanan components:

## Do not add

- Page subtitles or paragraphs explaining what the page does
- Dev/ops hints: docker, pnpm, worker, scrape scripts, API paths (`POST /epass/...`)
- Multi-sentence navigation hints ("Open from District", "Choose a consigner above")
- Placeholder text like "Content coming soon"

## Empty states

One short, non-technical line only, for example:

- `No data available`
- `No consigners found`
- `No consignee lines found`
- `No challan lines found`

No instructions on how to fix or populate data.

## Error states

- Short title: `Unable to load data` (or similar)
- Optional plain error message from the API
- `Retry` button only — no setup commands

## Allowed

- Table column headers and filter labels
- Report metadata values (report date, scraped at, row counts)
- Pagination counts (`Showing 1–50 of 279`)
- Status badges (`pending`, `partial`) on data cells
- Functional navigation links without explanatory prose

## EpassReportMetaBar

- Metadata fields only (report date, portal generated, scraped at, rows)
- No `subtitle` prop for page descriptions
- No-data: single line `No data available` — no scrape how-to text
